Toyota to Cut Board to 11 From 27 Members, Nikkan Kogyo Says

-- B y   M a k i k o   K i t a m u r a
-- 
2011-03-07T07:41:57Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-07/toyota-to-cut-board-to-11-from-27-members-nikkan-kogyo-says.html
  Toyota Motor Corp. (7203)  will cut its
board to 11 members from 27, the Nikkan Kogyo Shimbun reported.  Executive Vice President Yoichiro Ichimaru will become an
auditor, Vice Chairman Katsuaki Watanabe adviser and Vice
Chairman Kazuo Okamoto president of truck-making affiliate Hino
Motors Ltd., the newspaper said. Yoshimi Inaba, president of
Toyota Motor North America Inc., will retire, and three managing
officers including Toyota Motor Manufacturing Canada Inc.
Chairman Ray Tanguay will be promoted to a new executive class
with operational duties, Nikkan Kogyo said.  Excluding Ichimaru, Toyota will retain five executive vice
presidents, the newspaper said.  The changes will be subject to shareholder approval in June,
the report said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Makiko Kitamura in Tokyo at 
 mkitamura1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
